#Factores

arr.personas<-sample(c("M", "F"), 15, replace = T)
arr.personas
fct.personas<-factor(arr.personas)
fct.personas
fct.personas<-factor(arr.personas, 
                     levels = c("M", "F"),
                     label=c("Hombre", "Mujer")
                     )
fct.personas
levels(fct.personas)
table(fct.personas)
freqq<-table(fct.personas)/length(fct.personas)
freqq
barplot(freqq, 
        main="Tabla Freq Relativa",
        xlab="Genero",
        ylab="Propocin",
        col=c("cyan", "pink"),
        space = c(0),
        names.arg = c("Masculino", "Femenino"),
        ylim=c(0, 0.7))
